post_text:
MMCRU 7th & 8th Parents,

We will now be providing a JH practice shuttle for all students participating in football and volleyball during our hybrid learning schedule. A shuttle will leave Marcus at 2:45pm each day for practice in Remsen. Students who don't have class due to our hybrid schedule can be dropped off in Marcus to make the shuttle to Remsen. A shuttle will still be provided after practice at 5:00pm to bring students back to Marcus. Parents can still drop their child off in Remsen if they choose not to ride the shuttle. Practice will begin each day at 3:30pm.

Thank you for your patience and understanding

Go Royals!!!

post_text:
MEET: Beth Ebert. Mrs. Ebert will be the high school Spanish teacher. Welcome Beth!

"My name is Beth Ebert. I live in Marcus with my husband, Rodney; we are "empty nesters". Our blended family includes five children and six grandchildren. I have degrees from Briar Cliff College, Morningside College, and the University of South Dakota. I have taught at MMC, Cherokee, and most recently River Valley. Besides teaching Spanish, I enjoy playing golf, playing the piano, and spending time with friends and family in my She Shed. I am super excited to be teaching at MMCRU so I can teach the students of my first students! Let's have a great year!"
#WelcometoMMCRU #loyalroyal

post_text:
MEET: Nick Long. Mr. Long will be an additional teacher to our Industrial Technology program. Welcome Nick!

"My name Nick Long and I am excited to be the second Industrial Technology Teacher here at MMCRU. I
am a 2014 graduate of Wayne State College and this will be my 6th year teaching. I spent my first 5
years teaching at George-Little Rock CSD before moving to the Marcus area. I enjoy the challenges of
creating things and working with my hands whether its woods, metals, or solving engineering issues in
CAD classes. When I’m not working at school or swinging a hammer in construction during the summer,
you can find me hanging out with friends on the golf course or enjoying some type of outdoor activity. I
am very excited to start my first year at MMCRU and look forward to growing and expanding the
excellent industrial trades program we have here."
#WelcometoMMCRU #loyalroyal

"Hey there! I’m Amber Van Regenmorter and I will be teaching Kindergarten through 4th grade general music in Marcus and Remsen. I graduated from Morningside College in December of 2019. MEET: Emma Davis. Ms. Davis will be our 5-12 Band Teacher. Welcome to MMCRU!

"Hi! I'm Emma Davis, and I will be teaching 5-12 Band this upcoming school year! I'm originally from Newell, Iowa, and I just graduated from Iowa State University this spring. While I was there, I had the opportunity to participate in a variety of band activities, including Marching Band, Pep Band, Wind Ensemble, and Percussion Ensemble. I'm looking forward to meeting all of you as we begin the school year!
Go Royals!"

MEET: Ashton Connelly. Mrs. Connelly will be teaching 1st grade in Marcus. Welcome to MMCRU Ashton!

"My name is Ashton Connelly and I’m a recent graduate from the University of Northern Iowa. I have grown up with a love of sports, especially basketball, and during the summer when I am not working you can always find me out on the golf course and in the fall at Kinnick Stadium cheering on the Hawkeyes. I love being out on the lake and spending time with friends, family, and my two dogs Riley and Herky. I recently got engaged and have been busy spending time planning our wedding. I’m excited to start my teaching career at MMCRU as a first grade teacher and look forward to a great school year!"m

MEET: Curt Gengler. Mr. Gengler will be one of our new PE teachers in the Remsen building. Welcome to MMCRU.

"My name is Curt Gengler, I live outside of Merrill, Iowa. I have a wife named Kari (who teaches Kindergarten at LeMars Community), Keegan (8th grade) and Kenley (3rd grade). My family lives on an acreage where my kids are the 7th generation to live on that land! Prior to teaching here at MMCRU, I was a substitute teacher for 5 years and subbed at Remsen Union prior to the merger with MMC. I then taught at Sacred Heart, part of Bishop Heelan, for the last 10 years as a PreK-8 Physical Education teacher and coach. I am excited to be back in Remsen and excited to be a part of the Royals Family!"

"Hi! My name is Megan Kramer and I live in Orange City with my husband, David and our daughter, Harper. We love the outdoors so we spend a lot of time camping, fishing and swimming in the summer. There is nothing better than when you see a child have that “aha” moment when learning a new skill. I am so excited to start my new adventure at MMCRU and teaching Preschool!"

Current and Potential Substitute Teachers:

MMCRU is excited to share with you some changes to the substitute authorization process in the state of Iowa. Please click on this link: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XUeWtV3hTna__iNRvdfiNmkuJ_cdqWBESH9xh_fXPxc/edit for more information related to the changes. post_text:
MMCRU Students, Parents, and Community Members:

On Wednesday, July 1, the weight rooms in Marcus and Remsen will reopen to the public and to student-athletes under coaching supervision. However, a few new guidelines will apply. They are listed below. We greatly appreciate you following these new guidelines as they will help ensure a safe and healthy environment. Please make the school aware if these guidelines are not being followed.:
Do not enter the weight room if you are exhibiting any of the following symptoms:
Temperature >100.3F
Fevers
Chills
Cough
Muscle aches
Headache
Sore throat
Runny nose
Nausea
Vomiting
Diarrhea
Loss of taste or smell
No more than 10 people in the weight room at a time
Time limit for being in the weight room is 1 hour
Maintain social distancing of 6 feet
Clean your machine/weights after use
No use of water fountain (please bring water bottle)
Restrooms can be used
Wash your hands
The following specific times will be blocked off for our MMCRU’s strength and conditioning program at the Marcus weight room.
6:15-9:00 am on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday

post_text: MMCRU would like to inform you that a student-athlete on our high school softball team tested positive for COVID-19 on Sunday. The district has been in constant communication with public health over the past couple of days. All student-athletes, parents, and coaches have been contacted with how to proceed following guidance from public health. No spectators were exposed. No high school softball practices or games will take place until Wednesday, July 1 at the earliest. We have encouraged our players and coaches who were in close contact with the student-athlete to quarantine themselves for 14 days from last exposure and to be tested for COVID-19. The district encourages all community members to continue to practice safe habits including social distancing, staying home when ill, regularly taking your temperature, avoiding interaction with sick individuals (if possible), avoiding large gatherings of people, and following any other guidance from your family doctor/public health. If you have any questions please contact your local health care provider or public health. Thank you

MMCRU Counseling Dept.
May 4 at 6:44 PM ·

This is just another reminder for all students signed up for the April ACT Test to get signed up for the June test location at Marcus. The deadline to sign up for the June test is MAY 8th!

If you cannot make the June test date work, you can also select the July test date, but you will need to select a different location than Marcus. If you have any questions please let Mrs. Schroeder know or otherwise feel free to always call ACT for assistance.

If you were a junior signed up using a school voucher, please make sure you sign up for a different test date in order to not lose this credit.

Thank you.

MMCRU Community Members:
Earlier this week, the governor made a proclamation allowing fitness centers, health clubs, health spas or gyms to open on a very limited basis. Although this is the case for private fitness centers, according to the Department of Education, all schools are closed until June 1, and school facilities are off limits even though relaxed details have been put in place for private health centers. Until that time, the MMCRU fitness centers/weight rooms in both Marcus and Remsen will remain closed.

MMCRU Community Members:
Earlier this week, the governor made a proclamation allowing fitness centers, health clubs, health spas or gyms to open on a very limited basis. Although this is the case for private fitness centers, according to the Department of Education, all schools are closed until June 1, and school facilities are off limits even though relaxed details have been put in place for private health centers. Until that time, the MMCRU fitness centers/weight rooms in both Marcus and Remsen will remain closed.

post_text:
MMCRU,
We are sorry to notify you: Today Governor Reynolds announced that Iowa Schools will not reopen this year. MMCRU will continue to provide Voluntary Continuous Learning opportunities through May 27, which is the last scheduled day for the 2019-2020 school year. Please contact your children’s teachers with any needs you may have with their at-home learning. We will continue to provide paper packets that can be picked up each week on Monday’s & Thursday’s from 11am-1pm. Please contact the building your child attends if you have any further questions. We miss you all and want to make sure we stay connected with you and support you the best way we can during this unprecedented time. Take care and stay safe!

MMCRU Administration

MMCRU,

We miss you all and want to make sure we stay connected with you and support you the best way we can during this unprecedented time. Take care and stay safe!

MMCRU Administration

MMCRU Residents:

We have good news today! MMCRU has been approved for the summer lunch program by the USDA, so we can distribute free Grab N Go lunches starting on Monday. We will distribute only on Mondays and Thursdays between the hours of 11am to 1 pm. from the entryway at MMC Elementary and the RU school building. All students PK-12 are eligible for free food through this program. We will give you more information as it becomes available to us regarding this program.

post_text:
MMCRU Students, Parents & Residents:

MMCRU will not be able to distribute Grab N Go lunches at either the MMC or RU school sites as was previously communicated. This is because neither the MMC or RU districts qualify for the summer hot lunch program according to current USDA rules, because neither school building is located in an area with a with a 50% or higher rate of students who qualify for free/reduced lunches. Obviously with the current COVID-19 situation, rules are changing day-by-day, so if these rules change we will let you know. But as for now, no lunches can legally be served from our school buildings. We are sorry for any confusion we may have created.

Dan Barkel, Superintendent
MMCRU Community Schools
Marcus Office: 712-376-4171
Remsen Office: 712-786-1101

post_text: Due to the increasing spread of COVID-19 in our state and nation, beginning at 3 p.m. on Thursday, March 19, the MMCRU buildings in Marcus and Remsen will be going on full lockdown. We will only have office staff members available to answer phones from 7 a.m. until 1 p.m. on Mondays and Thursdays only and we are discouraging visitors. We will continue to have a grab-n-go breakfast/lunches available for distribution on Mondays and Thursdays from 7 a.m.to 9 a.m., and 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. from the entryway at the Marcus Elementary and Remsen school buildings. Thank you for your cooperation and we encourage you to stay home and practice healthy habits.

We will continue to have a grab-n-go breakfast/lunches available for distribution on Mondays and Thursdays from 7 a.m.to 9 a.m., and 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. from the entryway at the Marcus Elementary and Remsen school buildings. Thank you for your cooperation and we encourage you to stay home and practice healthy habits.

post_text:
Attention to all students taking courses through Northwest Iowa Community College (NCC):
“There will be no disruptions in current online classes. Both current high school and college students should proceed as normal. High school students are expected to continue their college online courses even if their high school is not in session. Parents and guardians, this is very important for you to understand. Please encourage your student to continue to participate in their online class because non-participation would have significant influence on your child’s grade (see the course syllabus for specific information on non-participation). It could also affects child’s long-term college GPA.

High School College Programming – if you have do not have access to the internet, please call NCC and ask for the Online Team. All high school CNA classes are suspended for the time being. All high school automotive students, and other face-to-face high school students, should await direction from their instructor.”

For more information visit:
https://nwicc.edu/covid19update/

post_text: Another big congratulations to our Large Group Speech Readers Theatre students for making it to All-State Speech this year. For Readers Theatre, the students act out a scene or small play with a script but without the use of costumes or props. The students chose to perform, "30 Horrible Catastrophes of Middle School." In order to be selected for All-State, the group had to be deemed one of the "outstanding" performances of the day, at the State competition. This is a huge achievement for our speech program and our school! #broughthomethebanner #loyalroyal

Our Middle School participated in - You Be The Chemist - Hosted by the NWAEA. There were 15 teams of 4 at the competition and we had 13 of 15 teams.

We had two teams place in the top 3 teams! Elsie, Kylie, Clint and Max got 2nd overall and Kaden, Jordan, Cody and Hayven got 3rd.

IASB School Improvement Needs Assessment Survey

MMCRU Royals
February 21 at 2:20 PM ·

Our school district has requested a Needs Assessment Survey conducted by the Iowa Association of School Boards (IASB). The survey is designed to help us assess our strengths and areas of needed improvement, with a focus on improved student achievement. We would like your opinions and judgments in response to the brief survey linked below. The survey takes an average of 9 minutes to complete. All responses are anonymous.
Just click the link below, or paste it in your browser and follow the instructions. Thank you for your participation and helping to make improvements for our students. Please reply with any questions.

http://lsurvey.ia-sb.org/index.php?r=survey/index&sid=91917&lang=en
